summary:
3. Decides to review all measures six months from the adoption of this resolution, with a view to modifying or lifting them, dependent on Liberia's progress;

4. Extends the mandate of the Panel of Experts for 12 months to:
	* Conduct assessment missions to Liberia and neighbouring States;
	* Investigate and compile reports on the implementation of measures on arms;
	* Provide midterm and final reports to the Council;

5. Requests the Secretary-General to reappoint the Panel of Experts, with two members, and make necessary arrangements to support its work;

6. Calls upon all States and the Government of Liberia to cooperate fully with the Panel of Experts;

7. Recalls that the Government of Liberia is responsible for controlling the circulation of small arms;

8. Requests the Government of Liberia to conduct a needs-based assessment for future weapons purchases;

9. Encourages coordination and exchange of information among Governments in the region;

10. Urges the Government of Liberia to adopt and implement legislation to combat illicit trafficking of arms;

11. Encourages the international community to support Liberia's reform efforts;

12. Encourages the Government of Liberia to cooperate with the Kimberley Process;

13. Reaffirms the need for UNMIL and UNOCI to coordinate their strategies and operations;

14. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
